{"TopicId":174050,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Losing rover control on Duna \u0026lt;KSP - 1.4.1\u0026gt; \u0026lt;Solved\u0026gt;","CreatedByName":"Tweak[Box]","CreatedById":184277,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-18T12:23:44Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Tweak[Box]","CreatedById":184277,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-18T12:23:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve been trying to bring a polar surveying satellite and a scanning rover to Duna in one payload. It\u0027s all good until I decouple my satellite with 2 Communotron 88-88 and the rover with a HG-5, a Communotron 16, and a\u00A0Communotron 16-S\u00A0suddenly goes \u0022\u003Cem\u003Elimited probe control\u003C/em\u003E\u0022. Isn\u0027t the rover \u003Cstrong\u003Esupposed\u003C/strong\u003E to have relay connections to my satellite? Or am I still supposed to have direct Kerbal link?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere are pictures of the satellite ,rover and the final stage:\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://imgur.com/a/uqggO\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EAlbum\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEDIT:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Thanks for reminding me that there\u0027s a difference in antennas....\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:0.0:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_shocked.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:0.0:\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:confused:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_huh.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:confused:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-04-18T13:01:43Z\u0022 title=\u002204/18/2018 01:01  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EApril 18, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Tweak[Box]\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003EFixed album link\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"GuyWithGlasses","CreatedById":180330,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-18T12:40:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo you have any relay antenna in the sat? (The link doesn\u0027t work for me).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"LameLefty","CreatedById":57336,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-18T12:57:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223357526\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022174050\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221524054224\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022184277\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Tweak[Box]\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n31 minutes ago, Tweak[Box] said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve been trying to bring a polar surveying satellite and a scanning rover to Duna in one payload. It\u0027s all good until I decouple my satellite with 2 Communotron 88-88 and the rover with a HG-5, a Communotron 16, and a\u00A0Communotron 16-S\u00A0suddenly goes \u0022\u003Cem\u003Elimited probe control\u003C/em\u003E\u0022. Isn\u0027t the rover \u003Cstrong\u003Esupposed\u003C/strong\u003E to have relay connections to my satellite? Or am I still supposed to have direct Kerbal link?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere are pictures of the satellite ,rover and the final stage:\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022http://imgur.com/https://imgur.com/a/uqggO\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EAlbum\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYour album link isn\u0027t working, but I think you\u0027ve got things backwards. You need the relay antenna on the satellite so it can, you know, \u003Cstrong\u003Erelay \u003C/strong\u003Ethe comms from Kerbin to your rover.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlternatively, you can use a crewed satellite with two pilots (one for the vessel, one to remotely control the rover) and a command pod with 2 control points to do the same thing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tweak[Box]","CreatedById":184277,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-18T12:59:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223357536\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022174050\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221524055248\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022180330\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022GuyWithGlasses\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n34 minutes ago, GuyWithGlasses said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo you have any relay antenna in the sat? (The link doesn\u0027t work for me).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOMG \u0026lt;facepalm\u0026gt;...... That\u0027s what I\u00A0forgot! Thanks man! Also fixed the link!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-04-18T13:15:32Z\u0022 title=\u002204/18/2018 01:15  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EApril 18, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Tweak[Box]\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"bewing","CreatedById":154251,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-18T13:11:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe correct link is\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://imgur.com/a/uqggO\u0022 ipsnoembed=\u0